One of the most significant advantages of limiting car usage is the reduction in greenhouse gas emissions. Cars are a major contributor to air pollution and the release of greenhouse gases, which have detrimental effects on the environment and public health. In Europe, passenger cars alone are responsible for 12 percent of greenhouse gas emissions, and in some car-intensive areas in the United States, this number can be as high as 50 percent (Rosenthal, 2009). By reducing car usage, we can significantly decrease these emissions and mitigate the negative impacts of climate change. 

