I am writing to express my support for keeping the Electoral College as the method of selecting the President of the United States. While there are arguments for changing to a popular vote system, I believe that the Electoral College provides several important benefits that should be considered.

One of the main advantages of the Electoral College is the certainty of outcome that it provides. In the history of the United States, disputes over the outcome of an Electoral College vote have been rare. This is because the winning candidate's share of the Electoral College usually exceeds their share of the popular vote. This ensures that the election results are clear and accepted by the majority.

