Additionally, limiting car usage can have economic benefits. In Paris, for instance, a partial driving ban was enforced due to smog. This led to a 60 percent decrease in congestion in the city. By reducing the number of cars on the road, traffic flows more smoothly, saving time and increasing productivity. Delivery companies may complain about lost revenue, but this can be mitigated by implementing alternative transportation methods like bike sharing programs or car-pooling apps. Overall, limiting car usage can help boost the economy and improve the efficiency of transportation systems.

