Furthermore, limiting car usage can help reduce greenhouse gas emissions, which contribute to climate change. The United States, being one of the prime car cultures in the world, has seen a decrease in the number of miles driven per person in recent years. This shift in behavior, driven by factors such as the recession and changing attitudes towards transportation, has not only reduced emissions but also prompted car companies to rethink their strategies and focus on more sustainable alternatives.

