In conclusion, while the Electoral College may have its flaws, the practical reasons for keeping it outweigh the arguments in favor of changing to a popular vote system. The Electoral College provides certainty, ensures a president with trans-regional appeal, encourages thoughtful voter participation, balances the weight of large states, and avoids run-off elections. It is a system that has stood the test of time and continues to serve the interests of our nation.

Thank you for considering my perspective on this matter.

